* - The maximum contents apply to the product in the state in which it is offered to the consumer. For products not covered by the table set out in Part II, which are produced from ingredients with limits laid down in this Regulation and which have been dried, diluted, processed or compounded by one or more ingredients, the maximum permitted levels must be deducted from the specific concentration and dilution factors, in relation to the limits established for the ingredients, which must be provided at the time the competent Sanitary Authority so requests. When applying the ceilings set out in Part II to foods which are dried, diluted, processed or composed of one or more ingredients, the following shall be taken into account: (a) changes in concentration of the pollutant caused by drying or dilution processes;
* changes in concentration of the pollutant, caused by the processes of transformation;
* the relative proportions of the ingredients in the product;
* the analytical limit of quantification.
* - The manufacturer of the product must communicate and justify the information on the proportion of the ingredients in the product (if necessary), as well as the specific factors of concentration or dilution, at the request and within the period required by the competent Sanitary Authority for each of the drying, dilution, processing and / or mixing operations in question, or for the dried, diluted, processed and / or compounded food products. If the manufacturer of the product does not report the required concentration or dilution factor, or if the competent authority considers that this factor is inadequate, taking into account the justification provided, that authority shall define this factor on the basis of the available information.
* - Criteria 1.6 and 1.7 shall apply provided no specific maximum levels have been established for these dried, diluted, processed or compound foodstuffs.
* - Foods which do not comply with the maximum levels set out in the annexed tables shall not be used as food ingredients.
2 - Specific criteria
* - The maximum content is applied after washing the fruits or vegetables and separating the edible part as appropriate. In the case of potatoes, the maximum content is applied to peeled potatoes.
* - The maximum content refers to the edible part of thedry fruits.
* - In the case of cereals, the maximum content applies to:
* unprocessed cereals intended for human consumption;
* cereals intended for direct human consumption, descaling, polishing and / or processing where appropriate;
* to the bran if it is destined to the final consumer.

