Requirements for documents rearranged for registration of veterinary pharmacological preparations
List of documents required to consider the possibility of registration of veterinary drugs:
1. Application of the applicant, signed by the head, which indicates a specific request to the Central State Medical Center for registration (re-registration) or testing of the drug;
2.Materials on the experimental study of the drug (Appendix 1) with the results of their own research, containing a detailed description of research methods (indicating their sensitivity), tested doses and results obtained.
Materials for the experimental study of the drug should include: - literature reference of the drug;
- a description of the dosage forms of the drug, indicating all components of the drug and their purpose;
- a report on the study of the toxicity of the drug (acute, subchronic and chronic);
- scheme of technological preparation of the preparation;
- a report on the study of individual effects of the drug (teratogenicity, mutagenicity, carcinogenicity, allergenicity);
- a report on the study of the pharmacokinetics of the drug;
-report to study the timing of the removal of residual amounts of active substances of the drug from the body of animals;
