2, Appendix JORF August 7, 2003
Created by Decree n ° 2003-768 of August 1, 2003 - art. 2 (V) JORF 7 August 2003
For the purposes of this section and the texts adopted for its application, the following definitions apply:
1 ° Transport: any movement of animals by means of transport including loading and unloading of animals;
2 ° Place of departure: place where the animals are loaded for the first time in a means of transport, as well as any place where the animals have been fed and watered and have enjoyed a rest period of at least twenty-four hours, with the exception of any stopping or transfer point.
Is also considered to be the place of departure any approved assembly center, provided that, if it is more than fifty kilometers away from the first place of loading, the animals have enjoyed a sufficient period of rest and have been there if necessary, fed and watered;
3 ° Place of destination: the place where the animals are last unloaded, excluding any stopping or transfer point;
4 ° Travel: any movement of animals from the place of departure to the place of destination;
5 ° Stop point: place where the trip is interrupted to water, feed and rest the animals for at least twenty-four hours;
6 ° Rest period: continuous period during the journey during which the animals are not moved by means of transport;
7 ° Carrier: any natural or legal person transporting live animals either for his own account or for the account of a third party, or by making available to a third party a means of transport intended for transport of animals.
These transports must be of a commercial nature and be made for profit.
