## CHAPTER II

Competent Authority

## SECTION I

Skills and Plans
Article 6
(Competencies of the Competent Authority)
Within the scope of official controls, the Competent Authority is responsible for:
* a) carry out planning, development,
implementation, supervision and control of activities related to official controls and other official activities;
* b) establish specific technical standards for
official controls and other official activities, including the elaboration or adaptation of specifications harmonized with national and international legislation;
* c) authorize the installation and or modification of the units
productive, including those of living aquatic organisms;
* d) license and inspect production units, including
those of living aquatic organisms;
* e) certify fishery products for placement
on the market and in transit;
* f) certify feeds for aquatic animals in coordination
with the Competent Veterinary Authority;
* g) certify fishery products for non-food purposes;
* h) monitor biosafety plans at the units
production of living aquatic organisms in coordination with the Competent Veterinary Authority;
* i) promote health monitoring and certification
aquatic organisms in coordination with the Competent Veterinary Authority;
* j) ensure health monitoring and certification
aquatic plants in coordination with the Phytosanitary Authority;
* k) carry out research, analysis and evaluation programs
related to hazards and risks in aquatic organisms, fishery products and animal feed;
* l) carry out the verification and audit compliance
and the compliance with the hygiene and sanitary requirements of the production units, at all stages of the production chain, including distribution and trade;
* m) create and maintain a documentary record system
licensing, certification, laboratory analysis and other related processes;
* n) carry out training, research and dissemination actions
inspection activities for fish;
* o) perform internal audits and supervision;
* p) to process and decide on the hygienic infraction processes
-Sanitary;
* q) disseminate national and international legislation regarding
food safety, general and specific requirements of import markets and fish inspection;
* r) disseminate the list of production units and operators;
* s) provide laboratory analysis services related to

