Article 5
(Functions of the competent authority)
* The following are specific functions of the competent authority, in accordance with this law:
* * inspect and consequently certify the quality hygienic-sanitary fishery products for domestic consumption and export, as well as imported products;
* * periodically inspect boats and establishments in the fishing and aquaculture industry;
* * proceed with the approval of the conditions hygienic-sanitary boats and establishments and issue the respective authorizations;
* * elaborate and disseminate, according to the conditions hygiene and sanitary, the lists of fishing industry establishments and boats authorized to fish for consumption, including for export;
* * issue health certificates for internal consumption and export, in accordance with the health certificate models, approved by a joint executive decree of the Ministers of Fisheries and Health;
* * audit food security assurance systems (self-control) fishing industry establishments and boats;
* * require production data records.
* The functions of the competent authority are exercised by the services designated for that purpose in the organic statute of the Ministry of Fisheries, to supervise the fishing infrastructures and market studies, as established in the respective procedures manual.
